 {"id":"bd-yx9r.12","title":"Developer, operator, and acceptance-surface parity","description":"The upstream crate includes user/operator-facing surfaces beyond runtime APIs: CLI/console, tracing compatibility, test internals, examples, and a broader parity story across docs and smoke packs. The ANSI C port needs comparable operator/developer affordances if it is claiming real functional parity.","design":"This epic captures the non-kernel, non-protocol surfaces that determine whether the port is practically usable and supportable.","acceptance_criteria":"A. CLI/console/test-helper/examples/docs surfaces are represented explicitly.\\nB. Final crate-level acceptance is backed by logged smoke packs and an auditable parity report.\\nC. The backlog no longer treats docs/examples/operator flows as optional polish.","notes":"Primary upstream references: src/console.rs, src/bin/asupersync.rs, src/test_*.rs, README examples, and module-specific operator flows.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:49.808248302Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:35.129782549Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["acceptance","cli","conformance","core-parity","crate-parity","docs","e2e"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:49.808248302Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:21.139278268Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:22.270401342Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:23.383751974Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-yx9r.12.1","title":"Implement CLI, console, tracing-compat, and test-internals parity","description":"Port the user-facing and developer-facing helpers that are publicly exported or shipped upstream: CLI/console entry points, tracing compatibility hooks, test logging/NDJSON/test utility surfaces, and comparable diagnostics for running the system.","design":"This should produce real operator entry points and test-support modules, not just docs stubs.","acceptance_criteria":"A. CLI/console/tracing-compat/test-internals public surfaces exist with clear build/profile gates.\\nB. Tests cover logging/report formats, CLI error handling, and tracing compatibility behavior.\\nC. Smoke packs exercise the operator path with detailed logs and rerun guidance.","notes":"Depends on A2 and A3, plus lower-level runtime/service work as needed.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:51.488592152Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T21:52:12.843662883Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cli","console","crate-parity","test-internals"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:35.418742220Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.12","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:51.488592152Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:40:04.137634865Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.12.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:37.053670038Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
